                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d519</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">519</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-12-19T12:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="519" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.20293/12–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-19T12:00:00-05:00">December 19, 1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2014. Dept is withholding action on proposed Sino-American intelligence
                    organization pending receipt of Embassy’s comments. (Deptel 1899, Nov. 26, 8
                        p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d519fn3">See footnote 75, <ref target="#pg_679">p.
                            679</ref>.</note>) An early reply would be appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
